#. <section class="sutta" id="sn47.32"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn47.32:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 47"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 47"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn47.32:0.2"
msgid "4. Ananussutavagga"
msgstr "4. Not Learned From Anyone Else"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn47.32:0.3"
msgid "32. Virāgasutta"
msgstr "32. Fading Away"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "sn47.32:1.1"
msgid ""
"“Cattārome, bhikkhave, satipaṭṭhānā bhāvitā bahulīkatā ekantanibbidāya "
"virāgāya nirodhāya upasamāya abhiññāya sambodhāya nibbānāya saṃvattanti."
msgstr ""
"“Mendicants, these four kinds of mindfulness meditation, when developed and "
"cultivated, lead solely to disillusionment, dispassion, cessation, peace, "
"insight, awakening, and extinguishment."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "sn47.32:2.1"
msgid "Katame cattāro?"
msgstr "What four?"

msgctxt "sn47.32:2.2"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu kāye kāyānupassī viharati ātāpī sampajāno satimā, "
"vineyya loke abhijjhādomanassaṃ;"
msgstr ""
"It’s when a mendicant meditates by observing an aspect of the body—keen, "
"aware, and mindful, rid of desire and aversion for the world."

msgctxt "sn47.32:2.3"
msgid "vedanāsu … pe …"
msgstr "They meditate observing an aspect of feelings …"

msgctxt "sn47.32:2.4"
msgid "citte … pe …"
msgstr "mind …"

msgctxt "sn47.32:2.5"
msgid ""
"dhammesu dhammānupassī viharati ātāpī sampajāno satimā, vineyya loke "
"abhijjhādomanassaṃ."
msgstr ""
"principles—keen, aware, and mindful, rid of desire and aversion for the "
"world."

msgctxt "sn47.32:2.6"
msgid ""
"Ime kho, bhikkhave, cattāro satipaṭṭhānā bhāvitā bahulīkatā ekantanibbidāya "
"virāgāya nirodhāya upasamāya abhiññāya sambodhāya nibbānāya saṃvattantī”ti."
msgstr ""
"These four kinds of mindfulness meditation, when developed and cultivated, "
"lead solely to disillusionment, dispassion, cessation, peace, insight, "
"awakening, and extinguishment.”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn47.32:2.7"
msgid "Dutiyaṃ."
msgstr ""
